=== SESSION CREATE / TASK 11 COORDINATION ===

POST /sessions remains 501 (not implemented). Spec asked for rejection when default identity missing tokens once sessions exist. Implemented **session_identity_tokens_sufficient** exported from server crate: merges DB identity ciphertext presence with non-empty `agent_token` / `git_token` strings in session `params` (JSON). Task 11 should call this and return 400 when false.

=== AUTH-STATUS LOGIC ===

- No git token → git_token_status not_configured
- Git token, no token_expires_at → healthy (manual / no metadata)
- Expiry > now+5m → healthy with message
- Expiry within 5m → expiring_soon
- Expired + refresh ciphertext present → expired_refreshable
- Expired + no refresh + oauth_github|oauth_gitlab → expired_needs_reauth
- Expired + no refresh + otherwise → unknown
- agent_token_status: not_configured | healthy (no expiry metadata v1)

=== REPOSITORIES ===

- resolve_git_provider: oauth_github/oauth_gitlab from row → fixed provider; else require ?provider=github|gitlab
- GitRepoListError::Unauthorized → HTTP 401; BadGateway → HTTP 502
- Live client: GitHub GET api.github.com/user/repos; GitLab GET {base}/api/v4/projects?membership=true; PRIVATE-TOKEN header for GitLab

=== PATCH SEMANTICS ===

PatchIdentityRequest uses Option<Option<String>> per field: omitted = no change; JSON null = clear ciphertext; string = UTF-8 bytes in BYTEA (app-layer encryption still “later” per prior docs).

